caption.text:
Time waits for no man. The social project and interactive journal "#413Ways to be Successful" was created to change the way people define, perceive, and achieve success.  because I've always been intrigued by what makes "successful" people successful and what specifically did they do differently in order to achieve their success. I believe that success is completely subjective, and everyone defines and achieves it differently. 
I have a passion for helping people follow their own passions and interests, so this social project gives me an opportunity to collaborate with people around the world in order to view the limitless perspectives about success. I aim to create a culture that values the differences and diversities in opinions about success as well as the viewpoints of people around the world.

The number 413 was inspired by the Bible verse Philippians 4:13 which states, "I can do all things through Christ who strengthens me." My interpretation of this verse is that with the right balance of determination, diligence, and dedication, I can achieve anything I put my mind to.

My inspiration for compiling the list into an interactive user-created journal was simply seeing so many different methods of achieving success & noticing the similarities between them (for example: getting rid of fear, increasing one's focus, ignoring nay-sayers, following passion, etc.) The common habits amongst successful people inspired me to write my own list, but with a twist of my personal perspective from my own frame of reference. My own list will be released in the form of the 413 Ways to be Successful: Compilation Book, at a later date.

This project was created to remind everyone on their path to success that it can be reached in a countless number of ways but however we reach it, we have to ensure that we are aiming for our own definition of success, and not society's definition. The journals are available to give users ownership about their ideas and allow the opportunity to document their creative, unique ways to achieve success.

caption.text:
Dreams come true. 
I'm unbelievably excited to announce that starting on Monday I will be joining the @Instagram community team full time. 
I've been lucky enough to work closely with @josh, @jayzombie, @dantoffey  and @baileyelaine over the last six months while I've been at @Facebook, and the work they do is continually inspiring. As a result, the community that's formed on Instagram has come to mean something deeply personal for me as well. It has helped me become a better photographer, a better writer and truly a better person. I can't wait to dedicate myself to a helping this community grow and thrive. So here's to a new adventure—let's go!
